The paper proposes an evolutionary optimization method for multi-objective optimization problems. It leverages the complementary characteristics of two different scalarizing functions and maintains two co-evolving populations simultaneously. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, such as adversarial learning, which is also a characteristic of the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of optimization algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data structures and algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of control systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
